docs.lead_paragraph: The pressure for multiparty democracy seems to be fading in African politics, but many longtime leaders feel the need to go through the motions.
docs.abstract: News Analysis; presidential elections in Uganda are underway, and most expect Pres Yoweri Museveni to remain in power; in many recent elections across Africa, longtime leaders feel need to hold elections, despite predictable outcome.

headline.main: Instead of Democracy, Uganda Moves Toward Dictatorship Light
headline.print_headline: Uganda Moves Toward ‘Dictatorship Light’ Amid Elections
